{"lemma":"حَلُوباتٌ","slug":"حَلُوباتٌ","root":"ح.ل.ب","root_slug":"ح-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8804"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8804","headword_ar":"حَلُوبٌ","root":"Hlb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaluwbapN","text_ar":"حَلُوبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(of which the latter is the more common, TA) A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is milked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) both signify alike: (TA:) or the former is an epithet, signifying as above; and the latter is a subst., signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animal that is milked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, Mgh, Msb, TA;) though some say the reverse: or sometimes the former is used for the latter, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a milch camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: accord. to Meyd, the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel that is milked for the guest, and for the people of the tent or house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the former is used by some as a sing., and by others in a pl. sense: (IB, TA:) and [in like manner] the latter is applied to a single she-camel or ewe or she-goat, and to more: (K:) the pl. (of the latter, TA) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalaAy^ibu","text_ar":"حَلَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulubN","text_ar":"حُلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulobN","text_ar":"حُلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", supposed to be a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulubN","text_ar":"حُلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also occurs as a pl. epithet applied to ewes and to she-goats. (Lh, TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaluwbapN tuvomilu walaA tuSar~iHu","text_ar":"حَلُوبَةٌ تُثْمِلُ وَلَا تُصَرِّحُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A milch camel that gives much froth in her milk, and does not give pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear, milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a prov., applied to him who promises much, but performs little. (Meyd, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d~r~ato Haluwbapu Almusolimiyna","text_ar":"دّرَّتْ حَلُوبَةُ المُسْلِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The milch camel of the Muslims has yielded a copious supply of milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said when the dues of the government-treasury are in a good state. (IAar, Suh, TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalobaAnapN","text_ar":"حَلْبَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, signifies A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is milked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milch"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel; (A, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaluwbN","text_ar":"حَلُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalobaApN","text_ar":"حَلْبَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabuwtN","text_ar":"حَلَبُوتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalobaY","text_ar":"حَلْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabuwtaY","text_ar":"حَلَبُوتَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobaAnapN","text_ar":"رَكْبَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobaApN","text_ar":"رَكْبَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabuwtN","text_ar":"رَكَبُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobaY","text_ar":"رَكْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabuwtaY","text_ar":"رَكَبُوتَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fit to be milked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakuwbN","text_ar":"رَكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaluwbN","text_ar":"حَلُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the rest of the foregoing epithets, except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabuwtN","text_ar":"حَلَبُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which I nevertheless believe to be perfectly syn. with them, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalabuwtN","text_ar":"خَلَبُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~aAbN","text_ar":"خَلَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the S,] are also mentioned as having an intensive signification. (TA.) You say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN HalobaAnapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ حَلْبَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobaAnapN","text_ar":"رَكْبَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobaApN","text_ar":"رَكْبَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalobaApN","text_ar":"حَلْبَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabuwtN","text_ar":"رَكَبُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabuwtN","text_ar":"حَلَبُوتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobaY","text_ar":"رَكْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalobaY","text_ar":"حَلْبَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabuwtaY","text_ar":"حَلَبُوتَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabuwtaY","text_ar":"رَكَبُوتَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel that is milked and ridden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that yields abundance of milk and that is submissive to be ridden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) AZ mentions ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN HalobaAtN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ حَلْبَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter word in the pl. form; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN rakobaAtN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ رَكْبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [But"},{"kind":"page_break","n":625},{"kind":"text","text":"in each case I think that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlibN","text_ar":"حَالِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAjirapN HaluwbN","text_ar":"هَاجِرَةٌ حَلُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A summer-midday"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that draws forth the sweat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","IB","K","S","IAar","ISd","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}